75108822-bb8d-fb41-b51a-c4c44aea0a00.description	"<div class=\"intro-image image center full-width\" style=\"width:640px\">\n      <img src=\"http://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/Nest5.jpg\" width=\"640\" height=\"427\">\n  \n  </div>\n <p>It has been close to a year since the <a href=\"http://www.nest.com/\">Nest</a> \"learning\" thermostat was introduced to the public, bringing us one step closer to that elusive <a href=\"http://arstechnica.com/business/2012/03/the-five-technologies-that-will-transform-homes-of-the-future/\">home of the future</a>. Founded by the former senior VP of Apple's iPod division, Tony Fadell, along with his partner Matt Rogers, Nest Labs set out to create what is essentially the iPod of the thermostat world. The round, user-friendly device was initially met with excellent reviews, but were these based in reality or were they the result of some Apple-like hype?</p>\n<p>I like to think of myself as somewhat of a thermostat nerd. (Listen, it doesn't sound very exciting because it's not, but I like them). I am fascinated by thermostats and their usability, but I also don't like to spend too much money on them—unless the extra cost is worth it. Friends and Twitter followers have long asked me to evaluate higher-end thermostats, and I'm always examining the thermostats at other people's houses. So when I finally had the opportunity to install a Nest, I jumped at it.</p>\n<p>Now that I've been using the Nest for several months, I have a pretty good feel for its strengths and weaknesses—at least compared to what is typically available on the market. Is the Nest really worth the $250 it costs to obtain one, just so you can have a fancier way of turning the temperature up and down? I think so—especially if you're the \"convenience oriented\" type (that's PC for \"lazy\").</p><p><a href=\"http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2012/08/a-thermostat-that-learns-three-months-with-the-nest/\">Read 44 remaining paragraphs</a> | <a href=\"http://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2012/08/a-thermostat-that-learns-three-months-with-the-nest/?comments=1#comments-bar\">Comments</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~at/Jgvmmo8M68VUN6mGvaW8S6RYeLU/0/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~at/Jgvmmo8M68VUN6mGvaW8S6RYeLU/0/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~at/Jgvmmo8M68VUN6mGvaW8S6RYeLU/1/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~at/Jgvmmo8M68VUN6mGvaW8S6RYeLU/1/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a></p><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/arstechnica/features/~4/vdYSbKar1us\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>"
