f264e8fb-5c07-fa7a-beaa-9b8280112482.description	"<p><a href=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ie/archive/2012/04/03/pinned-sites-in-windows-8.aspx\">Pinned Sites in Windows 8</a> describes how site developers can provide a site icon (favicon) for their sites&rsquo; pinned site tiles on the Windows 8 Start screen. Many of you shared feedback that you&rsquo;d like to provide higher-resolution visuals to better depict your site brand on your users&rsquo; pinned site tiles. In <a href=\"http://preview.windows.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Windows 8 Release Preview</a>, you can to do that: we&rsquo;ve added the ability for you to provide a PNG tile image and specify the tile&rsquo;s background color.</p>\r\n<h3>Example</h3>\r\n<p>Below are examples of a pinned site tile using the site&rsquo;s favicon and automatically determined color (left) and high-resolution PNG with custom tile color (right):</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 8.25pt; font-style: italic;\"><img alt=\"Default tile for the Fresh Tweets demo\" src=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/cfs-file.ashx/__key/communityserver-blogs-components-weblogfiles/00-00-00-38-71-metablogapi/7317.FreshTweetsDefault.png\" /><img style=\"margin-left: 2em;\" alt=\"Tile for Fresh Tweets demo following @BenThePCGuy\" src=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/cfs-file.ashx/__key/communityserver-blogs-components-weblogfiles/00-00-00-38-71-metablogapi/0385.BenThePCGuy.png\" /></p>\r\n<h3>Markup</h3>\r\n<p><code>Meta</code> tags specify the tile&rsquo;s image and background color. Example:</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -4em; padding: 0 0.25in;\">\r\n<div style=\"color: black; background-color: #f0f0f0; padding: 0 4px 2px 4px;\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0 0 0 4em;\"><code><span style=\"color: blue;\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color: maroon;\">meta</span> <span style=\"color: red;\">name</span><span style=\"color: blue;\">=\"msapplication-TileImage\"</span> <span style=\"color: red;\">content</span><span style=\"color: blue;\">=\"images/benthepcguy-144.png\"/&gt;</span></code></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0 0 0 4em;\"><code><span style=\"color: blue;\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color: maroon;\">meta</span> <span style=\"color: red;\">name</span><span style=\"color: blue;\">=\"msapplication-TileColor\"</span> <span style=\"color: red;\">content</span><span style=\"color: blue;\">=\"#d83434\"/&gt;</span></code></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Tile images must be square PNGs 144px by 144px. For best results, we recommend using a transparent background, not a background that matches the tile&rsquo;s color. The tile color can be specified as a hex RGB color using CSS&rsquo;s <code>#rrggbb</code> notation, via CSS color names, or by the CSS <code>rgb()</code> function.</p>\r\n<p>See this behavior in action on our updated <a href=\"http://ietestdrive2.com/pinnedsites/\" target=\"_blank\">Fresh Tweets demo</a>.</p>\r\n<p><b>Note:</b> IE10 only downloads the tile image when the user pins the site to his or her Start screen so sites don&rsquo;t incur additional bandwidth costs.</p>\r\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\r\n<p>Internet Explorer 10 enables Web developers to create high-quality site-centric visuals for pinned site tiles, allowing sites&rsquo; brands to be better reflected on the Windows 8 Start screen and look more visually integrated with the rest of the app and content tiles. Developers need provide only one high-quality icon that Windows 8 will scale as needed for devices running at different resolutions.</p>\r\n<p>Sites can also share notifications and offer jump lists for quickly navigating around the site. See <a href=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ie/archive/2012/04/03/pinned-sites-in-windows-8.aspx\">Pinned Sites in Windows 8</a> for how.</p>\r\n<p>We look forward to you adding these simple features to your Web site to maximize their impact in Windows 8.</p>\r\n<p>&mdash;Rahul Lalmalani, Program Manager, Internet Explorer</p><div style=\"clear:both;\"></div><img src=\"http://blogs.msdn.com/aggbug.aspx?PostID=10317370\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\">"
